3
00:00:04,890 --> 00:00:06,810
Five and one; evens win.

4
00:00:13,530 --> 00:00:14,780
Wow!

5
00:00:15,430 --> 00:00:19,270
They say it all depends on
the roll of the dice...

6
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:24,870
but luck's on your side, milord!
You're on a winning streak!

7
00:00:24,870 --> 00:00:25,960
Here.

8
00:00:29,390 --> 00:00:32,470
Take this for the sushi on the boat.

9
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:35,840
Wow! This is more than I paid, mister!

10
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:38,760
Don't worry. I'll win some more.

11
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:42,060
Wowee!

12
00:00:42,060 --> 00:00:44,980
We only dropped by to take
shelter from the rain!

13
00:00:45,910 --> 00:00:49,400
If I stay with you, I'll never go hungry!

14
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,030
Seriously! You're the savviest man in Wano!

15
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:59,660
I think the sake will taste good tonight.

16
00:01:00,990 --> 00:01:03,200
Now, place your bets!

17
00:01:06,150 --> 00:01:07,040
Odds!

18
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:11,960
Wow! You're not one to mess around, mister!

19
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:15,600
We've got a bet on odds!

20
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,440
All set.

21
00:01:32,940 --> 00:01:34,780
Here we go!

22
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:42,040
Oh!

23
00:01:47,490 --> 00:01:49,000
No-Sword Style...

24
00:01:49,670 --> 00:01:52,130
Dragon Twister!

25
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:11,060
Oh?! They were cheating!

26
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:14,230
How lame.

27
00:02:17,890 --> 00:02:19,910
Guys! Get out here!

28
00:02:24,090 --> 00:02:27,910
At least your hospitality
doesn't seem to be lacking.

29
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,630
Everyone! Get him!

30
00:02:42,790 --> 00:02:44,260
One-Sword Style...

31
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:51,060
Dragon Quake!

32
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:17,090
Whoa, wait a minute, mister!

33
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:22,990
We live our lives on the cusp of
evens and odds, just as with good and evil.

34
00:03:22,990 --> 00:03:26,080
Let's put an end to this here!

35
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:26,970
Okay?!

36
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:34,650
Now, manager, there was
an objection to the last game.

37
00:03:36,820 --> 00:03:40,700
Damn! Just take it! Don't ever come back!

38
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:31,210
Yikes! I was scared stiff!
Were you scared too, mister?!

39
00:05:31,210 --> 00:05:33,270
Could you shut up?

40
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:36,480
Wowee! That's mighty considerate of you!

41
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:40,570
You're so subtle in how you care for
my voice. How thoughtful. Thanks!

42
00:05:40,570 --> 00:05:44,690
Oh, sorry for not introducing
myself sooner. My name is Tonoyasu.

43
00:05:44,690 --> 00:05:47,830
Everyone calls me Yasu "the Sycophant."

44
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,450
Nice to meet you!

45
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:54,370
Oh my, you're captivating even
when you don't speak!

46
00:05:54,370 --> 00:05:58,250
You stud, you! The ladies
must be all over you, mister!

47
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:01,430
Why are you following me?

48
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:05,170
A thought struck me back
at the gambling house:

49
00:06:05,170 --> 00:06:08,890
"If I follow this man,
everything will be alright."

50
00:06:08,890 --> 00:06:12,790
An ordinary person wouldn't
have messed with those guys.

51
00:06:12,790 --> 00:06:18,440
They're yakuza thugs from the capital's
terrifying Kyoshiro Family.

52
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:21,440
Oh, what you did was staggering!

53
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:24,780
If I were a woman, I'd be weak at the knees!

54
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,450
What's the matter, mister?!

55
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,180
That looks familiar.

56
00:06:31,180 --> 00:06:36,200
You're so perceptive! What you see
in the distance is the Flower Capital!

57
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:39,290
And before that, you'll find
Ebisu, the Leftovers Town!

58
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:41,290
That's my hometown!

59
00:06:41,290 --> 00:06:44,500
Ebisu...? Like the god of fortune, huh?

60
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:49,430
Why is it named Ebisu, you wonder?
You'll see once you get there!

61
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:57,290
I'll take one, too!

62
00:06:57,290 --> 00:06:58,230
Coming right up!

63
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,490
He doesn't look familiar...

64
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:04,110
Hmm... It sure is popular though...

65
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,780
That squirt...

66
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:10,650
Doesn't he know who's turf this is?

67
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,810
We oughta show him...

68
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:23,920
Strike the iron!

69
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,930
Haul the stone!

70
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:44,770
If you can't work...

71
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:47,520
you should just die...

72
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:50,030
and get out of the way!

73
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,800
I-Is this it?

74
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:18,140
By hauling five big blocks of rock,
you get one millet dumpling!

75
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:23,900
Are you too decrepit to earn
your own food, old man Hyo?!

76
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:27,750
Death is finally closing in on you!

77
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:33,530
I worked all day...

78
00:08:33,530 --> 00:08:36,700
Huh?! What'd you just say?!

79
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,700
The punishment for talking back to a guard...

80
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:45,170
is dismemberment!

81
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:47,120
Next!

82
00:08:48,190 --> 00:08:52,340
Old man Hyo! Don't fight. Save your energy!

83
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:53,900
Or you're gonna die!

84
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:58,140
Oh, four exchange tickets!

85
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:00,200
Well done!

86
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,110
Move! Move! Move! Move! Move!

87
00:09:11,110 --> 00:09:13,320
Outta my way!

88
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:21,240
You guys are in my way!
Do you wanna get run over?!

89
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,870
Watch it, Jaggy!

90
00:09:24,620 --> 00:09:26,620
I'll run you over, too!

91
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,610
Wait, wait! It's already full! That's it for today!

92
00:09:59,030 --> 00:10:01,410
Then, get another ship out here!

93
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:02,700
You slowpokes!

94
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,250
I-I'm sorry!

95
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:13,000
How many stones did they haul?

96
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,090
I stopped counting at 500...

97
00:10:15,090 --> 00:10:17,430
Huh?! What about the seastone?!

98
00:10:17,430 --> 00:10:18,260
It's on them!

99
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:24,100
They pulled that off even while weakened?!

100
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:29,020
What can they do when the cuffs come off?

101
00:10:29,020 --> 00:10:32,190
I finished my work! Give me food!

102
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:35,150
What?!

103
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,760
Whaaat?!

104
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:57,800
How much did they haul
to get that much food?!

105
00:11:02,550 --> 00:11:04,140
What's your problem?!

106
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:05,430
What're you looking at?!

107
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:08,350
I got one more than you!

108
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:10,390
You punk! I outpaced you!

109
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:13,650
Screw you! No way you beat me, Jaggy!

110
00:11:13,650 --> 00:11:16,650
Can't you even count, you stupid monkey?!

111
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:18,150
You bastard!

112
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:20,150
Damn you!

113
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:26,200
I thought they were both badly injured...

114
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:34,460
They work, eat, and sleep... They're fully
recovered after just a few days...

115
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:36,670
How do their bodies work?!

116
00:11:37,450 --> 00:11:40,670
How are we supposed to break their spirits?!

117
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,010
Say something to them!

118
00:11:43,010 --> 00:11:44,260
What?!

119
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:51,690
Ch-Chew your food!

120
00:11:51,690 --> 00:11:53,310
Are you their mother?!

121
00:12:07,580 --> 00:12:10,160
My dumplings...

122
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:21,920
Dammit!

123
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:31,890
Which prisoner ate all
the food we had in storage?!

124
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:34,390
It's Vice Warden Dobon!

125
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,350
Hippo!

126
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:42,820
Bring out the perpetrator!

127
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,740
Help...!

128
00:12:47,740 --> 00:12:50,200
Oh! Old man Hyo is trapped!

129
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,950
Crawl out of there, old man!

130
00:12:52,690 --> 00:12:54,210
Vice Warden!

131
00:12:54,210 --> 00:12:55,920
They're behind bars now!

132
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:58,710
What?! What about the dumplings?!

133
00:12:58,710 --> 00:13:01,090
They ate them all...

134
00:13:01,090 --> 00:13:04,190
You guys just stood there and watched?!

135
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:06,470
They worked hard to earn that food,

136
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:10,480
so there wasn't a whole lot we could say...

137
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:15,490
How dare you disregard
the words of the vice warden!

138
00:13:20,610 --> 00:13:24,030
I can't really hear him since
the hippo closed its mouth...

139
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:25,200
Hippo?

140
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:27,200
Vice Warden Dobon...

141
00:13:29,310 --> 00:13:32,410
Bring the culprits here!

142
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,300
Vice Warden, here they are!

143
00:13:45,420 --> 00:13:47,300
These two are responsible!

144
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:58,770
– They're stuffed!
– They're stuffed!

145
00:13:58,770 --> 00:14:02,320
I've never seen anyone around
here with a full belly before!

146
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,190
They're so lucky!

147
00:14:04,190 --> 00:14:05,990
Damn you...!

148
00:14:05,990 --> 00:14:09,570
I'm a big eater, but thanks to you pigs,

149
00:14:09,570 --> 00:14:11,450
I only got three dumplings!

150
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:14,580
Look at this mouth! Think that was enough?!

151
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,750
Of course it wasn't!

152
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:19,820
Wait a minute...

153
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:22,090
I need to digest this...

154
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,060
– What?!
– What?!

155
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:47,360
I don't wanna see prisoners
looking so satisfied!

156
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:52,350
That was my food!

157
00:14:56,880 --> 00:15:00,250
Hey! Don't push your luck, you worms!

158
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:06,000
Listen up! If you mess with the guards...

159
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,550
the first offense will cost you your arms!

160
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:12,260
For the second, your legs!

161
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,890
And if there is a third,

162
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:18,100
you'll be sentenced to death!

163
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,930
You've been warned!

164
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:26,980
He's right! You guys have
no right to fight back!

165
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:32,700
Hey, we're weaklings at the moment,
thanks to the seastone.

166
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:35,700
All we did was work hard.

167
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:40,160
Your crime was...

168
00:15:45,610 --> 00:15:49,590
eating all my food!

169
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,260
Son of a...!

170
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:55,350
Jaggy!

171
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,810
Hippo!

172
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:09,150
I'll teach you discipline!

173
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,400
Whoa! He ate them!

174
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:14,610
Poor saps!

175
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:18,910
The inside of Vice Warden Dobon's
mouth is a slaughterhouse!

176
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:42,640
What happened?!

177
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:46,440
I've never seen the hippo go down like this!

178
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:56,840
Vice Warden Dobon?!

179
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:15,930
Look what you did! Just try
and escape the death penalty now!

180
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,760
Prove it.

181
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:21,640
What?!

182
00:17:23,090 --> 00:17:26,560
I'm saying you need to prove it!

183
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:35,700
Way to go, you guys!

184
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:38,570
This makes you heroes to the rest of us!

185
00:17:57,410 --> 00:18:02,600
Get some special soba!
Sangoro's special soba!

186
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:16,570
It's Sangoro's special soba!

187
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:21,120
I'd like to try some right away!

188
00:18:25,410 --> 00:18:28,730
Here! Thank you for waiting!

189
00:18:28,730 --> 00:18:31,250
Oh, it looks tasty!

190
00:18:45,790 --> 00:18:50,190
So good! This is insanely delicious!

191
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:52,270
Any word on Luffy?

192
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:55,940
He's at the prisoner
mining camp in Udon, right?

193
00:18:55,940 --> 00:19:01,890
It's pretty far from here, but I'm sure
he'll bust out before the big day.

194
00:19:02,870 --> 00:19:08,620
It's nice to eat your food again, Sanji!
I'm glad that you came back safely!

195
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:14,710
I don't care if you like it...

196
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:18,970
Orobi my lovely! How does it taste?

197
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,800
Well, it tastes incredible!

198
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:25,350
Orobi as a geisha is more incredible!

199
00:19:26,890 --> 00:19:28,140
Anyway...

200
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:31,980
the soba is good, but it's only drawing girls.

201
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:36,110
Attract samurai by whipping up
something spicy that pairs with sake!

202
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:45,570
What's with that look?! Don't you wanna
recruit more allies, you bum?!

203
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:52,730
Wait, Franky! Here come some male customers now.

204
00:19:53,670 --> 00:19:55,330
Pardon us.

205
00:19:55,330 --> 00:19:57,710
Excuse us, ladies!

206
00:19:57,710 --> 00:20:00,800
Hey guys, don't cut!

207
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:06,010
Huh?! You got something to say?!
Shut your mouth!

208
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:09,850
It's the Kyoshiro Family...

209
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:10,930
What?!

210
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,770
Hey, outta our way!

211
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:21,780
This place seems to be thriving, young man!

212
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,320
Yeah, I'm thrilled!

213
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:29,080
Are you guys customers?
If you wanna eat, get in line!

214
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:32,170
No, we just wondering something...

215
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:36,460
Who gave you permission to do business here?

216
00:20:39,670 --> 00:20:43,190
We're from the Kyoshiro Family,
and this is our turf...

217
00:20:43,190 --> 00:20:47,800
Unless you pay us, you're not
allowed to run a shop here!

218
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:50,680
Oh, is that so?

219
00:20:51,930 --> 00:20:55,350
Those people... I think they're...

220
00:20:56,670 --> 00:20:58,480
You know something about them?

221
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:03,820
Yes, the other day, I was at
the banquet hall of a man named Kyoshiro.

222
00:21:04,450 --> 00:21:08,280
Shogun Orochi is a coward!

223
00:21:12,830 --> 00:21:16,120
Sake! Bring me more sake!

224
00:21:19,460 --> 00:21:24,840
He was an extremely arrogant samurai.
It seems like he's a yakuza boss.

225
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:28,510
These men are likely his underlings.

226
00:21:29,470 --> 00:21:33,720
Hey, are you deaf?! I said you gotta pay up!

227
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:34,680
Why?

228
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:40,440
Why? Because if you don't, we can't protect
you if someone attacks your stand.

229
00:21:41,290 --> 00:21:45,280
I don't need your help. I'm pretty tough.

230
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,200
Here, thank you for waiting!

231
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,740
Thanks!

232
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:05,880
You think you're tough?

233
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:09,340
Then, just try to protect your shop!

234
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,140
Soba!

235
00:22:12,140 --> 00:22:13,680
Hey!

236
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:16,100
Don't eat the soba from this place!

237
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:31,410
Is she crying or laughing?

238
00:22:31,410 --> 00:22:33,910
My soba!

239
00:22:38,370 --> 00:22:41,920
Oh no! This will piss off Sanji
more than anything!

240
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:45,510
Beat it, ladies! The shop's closed for the day!

241
00:22:47,670 --> 00:22:50,640
Go, get outta here! He ran out of soba!

242
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:55,810
Come on! Just get lost!

243
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:03,060
Oh no! We'd better get outta the way!

244
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,570
Hey!

245
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:09,450
What do you want?

246
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:13,450
I'm gonna need you to finish your food...

247
00:23:14,130 --> 00:23:15,580
dear customer.

248
00:23:15,580 --> 00:23:18,750
Huh?! You wanna fight, punk?!

249
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:21,040
Hey! Suke! Kaku!

250
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,500
Yeah!

251
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:24,430
Let's rough him up!

252
00:23:25,540 --> 00:23:28,920
Hmm?! A fight?!

253
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:30,800
Go to hell!

254
00:23:36,590 --> 00:23:38,470
You bastard!

255
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:50,720
Ow, ow, ow...

256
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,120
Damn it!

257
00:24:03,210 --> 00:24:04,880
Die!

258
00:24:23,690 --> 00:24:25,210
Ow, ow, ow...

259
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,820
Big Bro!

260
00:24:31,690 --> 00:24:34,660
What with this soba cook?! He's so strong!

261
00:24:34,660 --> 00:24:37,160
That soba guy is so cool!

262
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:40,870
Sanji, save some for me!

263
00:24:45,170 --> 00:24:47,080
Here we go!

264
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:50,800
Stop! Dammit! What are you doing to me?!

265
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:54,500
Franosuke Iron...

266
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:02,830
Suplex!

267
00:25:11,150 --> 00:25:12,950
That carpenter, too?!

268
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:14,820
They shouldn't have done that!

269
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:29,710
Now, eat every last bite!

270
00:25:29,710 --> 00:25:33,460
You're gonna eat every bit
of soba you wasted!

271
00:25:34,170 --> 00:25:37,260
Here, eat up! Don't let any go to waste!

272
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:37,260
Big Bro! Big Bro!

273
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:39,690
What? You want some?!

274
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:43,120
You'll regret this!

275
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:47,850
Now, wakey wakey!

276
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:53,150
Nice doing business!

277
00:25:53,150 --> 00:25:58,330
Well, that's about what I expected,
but was it a good idea to kick their asses?

278
00:25:59,990 --> 00:26:03,250
Perhaps messing with them
wasn't the best idea...

279
00:26:03,790 --> 00:26:07,650
That long line of customers
scattered like roaches.

280
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:11,170
This is usually when
the big bruiser comes along.

281
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:18,970
She's the girl who had her soba knocked over.

282
00:26:18,970 --> 00:26:22,220
She's an oddball, crying and
laughing at the same time.

283
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:23,760
Huh? Wait a sec...

284
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:25,020
What is it?

285
00:26:25,020 --> 00:26:28,480
I've seen her somewhere before...

286
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:36,570
All right!

287
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:39,240
I made a killing!

288
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:41,820
I didn't think I'd sell this much!

289
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:47,950
What do you want?

290
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:52,290
Hey, so that's a medicine that
heals any kind of wound?

291
00:26:52,290 --> 00:26:54,340
Huh? Why, yes!

292
00:26:54,340 --> 00:26:57,010
This will stop bleeding and ease pain!

293
00:26:57,010 --> 00:27:00,880
This toad oil is a surefire remedy!

294
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:04,450
That's amazing!

295
00:27:05,020 --> 00:27:07,470
I met her at the shrine.

296
00:27:15,570 --> 00:27:20,030
Sorry about the trouble earlier.

297
00:27:20,030 --> 00:27:24,030
There was still soba left over.
Please have some!

298
00:27:24,030 --> 00:27:27,410
Whoa! Thank you!

299
00:27:41,510 --> 00:27:42,930
It's...

300
00:27:42,930 --> 00:27:47,280
I-It's delicious!

301
00:27:53,230 --> 00:27:56,440
You've really put on smile on my face!

302
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:58,010
I did?

303
00:27:59,860 --> 00:28:05,320
Your special soba is really popular,
so I couldn't wait to try it,

304
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:09,620
but the line was so huge!

305
00:28:09,620 --> 00:28:14,720
I waited with everyone for so long
that I'm already late for work.

306
00:28:16,630 --> 00:28:18,000
Work?

307
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,380
You work?!

308
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:25,800
Uh-huh! I worked hard and managed
to save enough money to buy the soba,

309
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,220
but it made me so sad
when it was knocked over.

310
00:28:28,220 --> 00:28:29,270
I'm happy now!

311
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:35,480
This is the best soba I've ever had!

312
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:41,820
Oh, yeah?! You like it that much? Thanks!

313
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:43,950
By the way, what's your name?

314
00:28:43,950 --> 00:28:47,200
It's Toko, but try to use
the "O" honorific at the start!

315
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,440
"O"?

316
00:28:48,870 --> 00:28:50,590
Otoko?

317
00:28:50,590 --> 00:28:52,490
Oh, like the word for "man"!

318
00:28:52,490 --> 00:28:55,490
I'm not a man! Otoko's just my name!

319
00:28:58,380 --> 00:29:01,300
I'm just a girl named Otoko.

320
00:29:03,010 --> 00:29:06,470
Isn't it funny? Isn't it amusing?

321
00:29:15,100 --> 00:29:17,810
People always say it's easy to remember!

322
00:29:20,850 --> 00:29:23,490
Uh-huh! Yeah! I'm sure I won't forget!

323
00:29:23,490 --> 00:29:25,280
That's a great name!

324
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:28,030
Totally!

325
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:32,830
Oh, it was delicious...!

326
00:29:32,830 --> 00:29:34,390
Thank you!

327
00:29:34,390 --> 00:29:37,200
Okay! Come back soon!

328
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,490
Uh-huh!

329
00:29:38,490 --> 00:29:42,670
Oh no! I'm really late! Very, very late!

330
00:29:44,130 --> 00:29:47,550
Oh, yeah! I'll be passing
through this street later!

331
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:49,760
The oiran's procession is today!

332
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:51,300
An oiran?!

333
00:29:51,300 --> 00:29:54,290
Toko, by any chance, are you a kamuro?

334
00:29:54,290 --> 00:29:56,990
That's right. I'm a kamuro!

335
00:29:56,990 --> 00:30:01,110
It's already started! I have to run!
Bye-bye! See you later!

336
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:04,820
The oiran's beautiful, so come have a look!

337
00:30:08,370 --> 00:30:10,590
See you!

338
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:13,910
Oh, man, she's so funny!

339
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:18,250
Toko's so cheerful. It's cute!

340
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:22,500
The oiran's procession I've heard so
much about will pass through here?!

341
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:24,300
Oiran?

342
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:26,170
Kamuro?

343
00:30:29,130 --> 00:30:32,050
An oiran is...

344
00:30:33,010 --> 00:30:36,430
Where did you come from,
you paper lantern-faced hag!

345
00:30:36,430 --> 00:30:37,480
Madam!

346
00:30:38,180 --> 00:30:41,230
Who'd you call a wrinkled,
paper lantern-faced hag?!

347
00:30:41,230 --> 00:30:44,570
I'll light your backside up, you little snot!

348
00:30:46,770 --> 00:30:51,780
An oiran is like the top idol
in Wano! A superstar!

349
00:30:53,190 --> 00:30:54,780
– Uh-huh! Uh-huh!
– Uh-huh! Uh-huh!

350
00:30:54,780 --> 00:31:00,160
Currently, there is only one oiran in the country!
The chosen woman's name is Komurasaki!

351
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:02,420
The woman of men's dreams!
An icon for women!

352
00:31:02,420 --> 00:31:06,050
Sophistication personified with
beauty to destabilize a nation!

353
00:31:11,140 --> 00:31:13,550
Even a god couldn't sully her nobility!

354
00:31:13,550 --> 00:31:17,050
She is the oiran Komurasaki!

355
00:31:17,780 --> 00:31:21,060
No way! Such a perfect woman can't exist!

356
00:31:21,060 --> 00:31:23,440
If you don't believe me, see for yourself!

357
00:31:26,860 --> 00:31:29,530
There! You hear that?!

358
00:31:29,530 --> 00:31:34,210
It's the cheering and the upbeat
music that surrounds her.

359
00:31:35,490 --> 00:31:38,590
The oiran is in procession to Orochi Castle!

360
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:42,290
There's a banquet for the shogun
at the castle tonight!

361
00:31:42,290 --> 00:31:47,070
The girl from earlier is a kamuro,
a young attendant to the oiran.

362
00:31:47,070 --> 00:31:49,920
Hmm, I see!

363
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:54,810
Orobi, I have good news for you! I ran
all around the Flower Capital looking for you.

364
00:31:54,810 --> 00:31:55,720
For me?!

365
00:31:57,270 --> 00:31:59,710
Congratulations!

366
00:31:59,710 --> 00:32:00,770
What?!

367
00:32:00,770 --> 00:32:03,730
You've also received a summons to the castle!

368
00:32:03,730 --> 00:32:07,590
You've dreamed of meeting
Shogun Orochi, right?!

369
00:32:07,590 --> 00:32:08,440
Yes!

370
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:12,570
Wow! That's our Robin!

371
00:32:12,570 --> 00:32:15,460
Now, let's go home and get ready!

372
00:32:15,460 --> 00:32:18,380
Yes! I can't wait!

373
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:32,220
Hey, straw hat guy!

374
00:32:32,220 --> 00:32:35,200
You're really something!
Which family are you from?!

375
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:40,190
Yesterday was so cathartic!
Every cell is talking about you!

376
00:32:40,190 --> 00:32:41,560
Leave me alone.

377
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:46,580
Don't be like that. Everyone here
adores the heck outta you!

378
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:48,610
Hmph... The cold shoulder it is, then.

379
00:32:49,570 --> 00:32:51,610
Sir Straw Hat!

380
00:32:54,160 --> 00:33:00,790
I'm so grateful that you saved
my worthless life yesterday!

381
00:33:00,790 --> 00:33:03,410
He was asking for it, so don't sweat it.

382
00:33:04,590 --> 00:33:06,960
Oh, yeah. You can have these!

383
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:09,670
No food, no work, right?

384
00:33:09,670 --> 00:33:15,580
Oh, no! Please don't! A good-for-nothing
like me can't accept those!

385
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:18,260
Of course you can. I insist.

386
00:33:19,510 --> 00:33:20,540
Later!

387
00:33:21,140 --> 00:33:24,230
I-I'll use them wisely!

388
00:33:24,230 --> 00:33:30,990
Thank you! Thank you! Thank you! Thank you!

389
00:33:30,990 --> 00:33:32,870
What a funny guy!

390
00:33:37,110 --> 00:33:38,630
Sir Luffy!

391
00:33:39,490 --> 00:33:42,080
Raizo! How did it go?!

392
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,200
Sorry for the wait.

393
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:48,490
I found the key to your seastone cuffs, but...

394
00:33:48,490 --> 00:33:50,360
it's under tight security.

395
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:54,300
Not only is it guarded,
but it's in a seastone box!

396
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:56,430
That said...

397
00:33:57,430 --> 00:34:01,220
I'll steal it at any cost.
Please give me a little more time.

398
00:34:01,220 --> 00:34:03,890
Okay! Got it!

399
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,810
Alright!

400
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:29,920
You again!

401
00:34:31,490 --> 00:34:35,670
You work so hard, Boss!

402
00:34:36,010 --> 00:34:39,540
Just how many millet dumplings
are you trying to earn, Boss?

403
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:41,220
I'm not gonna give you any!

404
00:34:41,220 --> 00:34:43,270
Cut it out! Caribou!

405
00:34:43,270 --> 00:34:49,010
Don't be like that! We're old friends, right?

406
00:34:50,490 --> 00:34:53,930
Wet-Haired Caribou of the Caribou Pirates.

407
00:34:53,930 --> 00:35:00,200
Luffy met this vicious, yet ill-fated,
pirate at the Sabaody Archipelago.

408
00:35:00,950 --> 00:35:08,410
He failed to take out the Straw Hat Pirates when he
raided the Sunny on her way to Fishman Island.

409
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:14,250
After arriving on Fishman Island,
he continued in his wicked ways...

410
00:35:14,250 --> 00:35:17,800
until he was defeated by Luffy and Pekoms.

411
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:24,140
Caribou would eventually reach the New World,
worming his way through various challenges.

412
00:35:27,270 --> 00:35:30,560
He discovered a new way of life there...

413
00:35:31,710 --> 00:35:34,270
but Drake suddenly
showed up and took him out.

414
00:35:34,950 --> 00:35:36,730
Caribou was then sent to Wano,

415
00:35:36,730 --> 00:35:42,500
and was forced into prison labor
at the mining camp in Udon.

416
00:35:47,690 --> 00:35:49,370
Oh, Boss...

417
00:35:49,370 --> 00:35:53,020
give me some, too!

418
00:35:53,020 --> 00:35:57,000
Millet dumplings for the needy!

419
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,610
No way! Do your own work!

420
00:35:59,610 --> 00:36:01,760
You're so cruel!

421
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:04,660
I heard about these seastone cuffs...

422
00:36:04,660 --> 00:36:09,770
They were made less potent
to allow prisoners to work still.

423
00:36:09,770 --> 00:36:12,850
Even so, I'm basically paralyzed...

424
00:36:12,850 --> 00:36:15,200
Push yourself harder!

425
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:19,460
You're so harsh, Boss.

426
00:36:19,460 --> 00:36:22,570
If you give me dumplings,
I'll be your henchman.

427
00:36:22,570 --> 00:36:25,990
I've been here way longer than you,

428
00:36:25,990 --> 00:36:29,000
so I know more about the place.

429
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:34,320
You'll do it, won't you, Boss?

430
00:36:36,710 --> 00:36:38,630
Shut up!

431
00:36:40,310 --> 00:36:44,590
You're planning to break out, right?

432
00:36:44,590 --> 00:36:47,060
Come on, let me in on it!

433
00:36:47,060 --> 00:36:48,140
Go away!

434
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:51,890
No slacking off!

435
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:58,650
A soba cook beat you?

436
00:36:58,650 --> 00:37:02,020
That's right! He was pretty tough!

437
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:05,110
He overpowered the three of us.

438
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:08,280
I'm gonna be busy today.

439
00:37:08,750 --> 00:37:12,960
I'm invited to Shogun Orochi's banquet...

440
00:37:13,380 --> 00:37:15,080
Contact Queen.

441
00:37:15,790 --> 00:37:19,840
Let's have him send an assassin.

442
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:22,390
That's likely to cause an uproar...

443
00:37:22,390 --> 00:37:24,340
I don't care!

444
00:37:23,890 --> 00:37:24,340
Yes, sir!

445
00:37:29,500 --> 00:37:30,640
Shogun Orochi...

446
00:37:30,640 --> 00:37:34,390
the oiran is heading this way now.

447
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:36,780
Excellent...

448
00:37:37,780 --> 00:37:39,480
Komurasaki...

449
00:37:42,490 --> 00:37:48,520
after today, you'll be mine!

